@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web

@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    SpikeRazor — Phase 7.0 SPIKE SCAFFOLDING (like CompositionProbe: 7.1
    decides what survives; the csproj/SDK recipe it proves is the keeper).

    THE first .razor file in the repo: compiled by the Razor source generator
    (Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Razor), NOT hand-translated. It exercises exactly the
    four things Phase 7.1's page rewrites need, in one component:
      1. markup   — a native element tree (div/span/input/button → the
                    view/text/input/button NodeTypes, same mapping as ever);
      2. [Parameter] — Title, supplied by the mount;
      3. @onclick — Clear, mutating state and re-rendering;
      4. @bind    — on the input, expanding (via Components.Web's built-in
                    BindAttributes — see the csproj note: own attributes are
                    IMPOSSIBLE without Components.Web because the compiler's
                    bind provider requires its BindInputElementAttribute type
                    to exist before reading ANY bind metadata) into
                    value + onchange — exactly BnInput's hand-written wire.

    The @using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web line is LOAD-BEARING twice:
    it scopes MouseEventArgs for @onclick AND puts Components.Web's
    BindAttributes tag helpers in scope — bind/event tag helpers are
    namespace-scoped like components, and without the @using the compiler
    SILENTLY emits the literal markup "<input @bind=...>" (zero diagnostics;
    verified empirically). 7.1 hoists this into _Imports.razor.

    The proof is SpikeRazorTwin.cs: the same component hand-written the
    pre-7.0 way. SpikeRazorTests mounts both through the real host session and
    asserts the patch streams are IDENTICAL — mount and after every dispatch.
    The inter-element whitespace this file compiles into Markup frames is
    handled by the renderer's Phase 7.0 Markup arm (slot, no patch, no view) —
    MarkupFrameTests pins that contract.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@

<div backgroundColor="#FFEEAA" padding="16">
    <span fontSize="24">@Title</span>
    <input placeholder="Type here..." @bind="_text" />
    <span>@_text</span>
    <button @onclick="Clear">Clear</button>
</div>

@code {
    /// <summary>The title text — the spike's [Parameter] proof.</summary>
    [Parameter] public string? Title { get; set; }

    private string _text = "";

    private void Clear() => _text = "";
}
